body:
&ldquo;Darkness can be suffocating but for those who don&rsquo;t breath it is peace&rdquo; - Kar Jarl


There is a deep, melodic voice in the darkness, it is as if the voice itself illuminates the void. There is defiantly something unsettling in the tone. The hairs stick up on the back of your neck. Your heart pumps a little faster and a slow crawling sense of dread hangs low in your stomach. You feel as if you are 5 and you are desperately lost on a beach or you have just slipped and barely caught your balance on a mossy rock. An uncontrollable trickle of panic filling your being drip by drip. 
 
&quot;Hello, Oh how far you have wandered to find yourself here with me&quot;
 
&quot;I bet that you think your reality is yours, a open lock, a solved riddle, the one thing that you can count on.&nbsp;It is YOUR reality right? Its not your friend&rsquo;s, your mother&rsquo;s, your uncle&rsquo;s or that rude sales clerk&rsquo;s.&quot; - The voice pauses letting the tone ring out in the emptiness. 
 
&quot;Let me ask you this, Does each entity have their own reality?  The paths that are forged by making thousands of individual choices and interactions are they predefined. A tangle of feelings and thoughts, luck and decisions nothing more?&quot; The question again hung, the voice pausing. 
 
&ldquo;Come a little closer and allow me to let you in on a secret only a few entities know.&rdquo;
 
&quot;Reality is not yours, hahaha&quot; The laugh was dark and bellowing, each heaving breath echoing and reverberating in the nothingness 
 
&quot;It&rsquo;s mine...&quot;
 
&quot;You see, what you define as &lsquo;reality&rsquo; is actually a tapestry of potential realities. The little control you do have is my gift to you. My divine gift that to many squander, wasting there life on poor choices and selfish desires. I don&#039;t let it bother me though, haha&quot; A short but ominous laugh rang out
 
&quot;They always get the fate they deserve as all strings have an end that is often frayed or tangled.&quot;
 
&quot;Have you ever felt the void?&quot;
 
&quot;It called you didn&#039;t it?&quot;
 
&quot;Tugging at you.&quot; 
 
&quot;Do you remember standing on a cliff?&quot;
 
&quot;At the edge of oblivion and having it pull you, beaconing you to jump. They say its the &#039;Call of the void&#039; HAHAHA&quot; the laugh had more ferocity now epic booming waves.
 
&quot;Its just me&quot; Said so matter of factly that it was as if it should have been obvious
 
&quot;I grow board of the darkness and have played with my threads weaving the fate that brought you here. You see I wish to compete, in the game you call the League of Legends for i have unfinished business... with a certain flamboyant individual...&quot;
